<i>adverb</i>: 한번 [한번], 좀 [좀], 장히 [장ː히], 엄청 [엄청], 아주 [아주], 사뭇 [사묻], 무척 [무척], 무지무지 [무지무지], 무지 [무지], 매우 [매우], 되게 [되ː게/뒈ː게] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>한번 [한번]</dt><br>
<dd>1. very; really; extremely</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 행동이나 상태 등을 강조함을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used to indicate that the speaker emphasizes a certain action or state of another person or thing.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 시험 삼아 시도함을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used to indicate that the speaker tries something.</dd><br>
<dd>3. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>기회가 있는 어떤 때.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used to indicate a certain time of opportunity.</dd><br>
<dt>좀 [좀]</dt><br>
<dd>1. a little</dd><br>
<dd>분량이나 정도가 적게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a small quantity or to a small degree.</dd><br>
<dd>2. a little</dd><br>
<dd>시간이 짧게.</dd><br>
<dd>For a short while.</dd><br>
<dd>3. please</dd><br>
<dd>주로 부탁이나 동의를 구할 때 부드러운 느낌을 주기 위해 넣는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A word chiefly used to soften a request for a favor or agreement.</dd><br>
<dd>4. very</dd><br>
<dd>상태의 정도가 보통에 가깝거나 그보다 약간 더 하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a degree being equal to or slightly above the average level.</dd><br>
<dd>5. very; pretty</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 강도나 정도가 대단히.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of intensity or degree being strong.</dd><br>
<dt>장히 [장ː히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. admirably; highly</dd><br>
<dd>타고난 마음씨나 인품, 의지 등이 훌륭히.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that one's inborn personality, character, willpower, etc., is admirable.</dd><br>
<dd>2. very; really</dd><br>
<dd>매우 또는 몹시.</dd><br>
<dd>To a considerable or significant degree.</dd><br>
<dt>엄청 [엄청]</dt><br>
<dd>very; extremely</dd><br>
<dd>양이나 정도가 아주 지나치게.</dd><br>
<dd>In an unusually large manner in size or degree.</dd><br>
<dt>아주 [아주]</dt><br>
<dd>1. very; so; extremely</dd><br>
<dd>보통 정도보다 훨씬 더 넘어선 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>To a degree much greater than normal.</dd><br>
<dd>2. entirely; utterly</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 행동이나 작용 등이 이미 완전히 이루어져서 바꾸거나 더 이상 어찌할 수 없는 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which it is impossible to change or do something because a certain action, etc., has already been done completely.</dd><br>
<dt>사뭇 [사묻]</dt><br>
<dd>1. all through</dd><br>
<dd>처음부터 끝까지 줄곧.</dd><br>
<dd>Continually from beginning to end.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quite</dd><br>
<dd>생각했던 것과 꽤 다르게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner quite different from what one presumed.</dd><br>
<dd>3. very</dd><br>
<dd>마음속 깊이 느껴지도록 매우.</dd><br>
<dd>So greatly as to be felt in one's heart.</dd><br>
<dt>무척 [무척]</dt><br>
<dd>very; extremely</dd><br>
<dd>다른 것과 비교할 수 없을 만큼, 매우, 아주, 대단히.</dd><br>
<dd>Very, extremely, exceedingly so that it is not comparable to any other.</dd><br>
<dt>무지무지 [무지무지]</dt><br>
<dd>extremely; really; very</dd><br>
<dd>놀랄 만큼 매우 대단하거나 엄청나게.</dd><br>
<dd>So hugely and extremely as to be surprising.</dd><br>
<dt>무지 [무지]</dt><br>
<dd>very; really</dd><br>
<dd>매우 엄청나고 대단하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Very hugely and extremely.</dd><br>
<dt>매우 [매우]</dt><br>
<dd>very; very much; greatly</dd><br>
<dd>보통보다 훨씬 더.</dd><br>
<dd>Much more than average.</dd><br>
<dt>되게 [되ː게/뒈ː게]</dt><br>
<dd>very; really</dd><br>
<dd>아주 몹시.</dd><br>
<dd>Extremely.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>